args: Xuan Zang, we've been walking for ages.\nWhere IS this guy? The one who can tell\nus about the Xihe, I mean.
I asked Yulong to have him\nmeet us in this area.
Ah, Xuan Zang. I see you are as\nfervent in your work as ever.
The same could be said for you, Xu Fu.
Indeed. Once a relic begins to affect\npeople's daily lives, it becomes an\nissue for all—not just sealers.
Is this Qilin a sealer as well?
No. However, he is most knowledgeable\nabout dragon-vein springs, and I would\ntrust him with my very life.
You always did give me too much credit.\nI'm little more than a mere hermit now.
Come, Xuan Zang. Let us speak frankly.\nWhat will you do about this situation?
I fear a solid plan eludes me, which is\nwhy I have come to seek your council.
Hmm. You cannot seal the relic, and yet\nyou also cannot leave it be. In that case,\nthere is but one solution...
A sealer must control it in perpetuity.
Exactly as I said: A sealer must keep\nthe relic in a stable condition on their\nperson at all times.
I hear the wisdom of your words, Xu Fu,\nbut the Xihe was enshrined here\ncenturies ago to stabilize the chi.
A sealer is fated to travel. Is it safe for us\nto take the Xihe away from here?

There is a way to transfer the Xihe's power
from faraway lands back to this place
through the use of dragon-vein springs.
But it would mean...
I knew I was right to trust in your wisdom!
Your plan is sound. I will collect the Xihe\nand maintain continuous control of it.
And I'm sure you are more than capable.\nHowever...
Are you certain you wish\nto shoulder this burden?
This will not be a thing you can abandon.\nOnce you take up the Xihe, you will\ncarry it for the rest of your days.
And if your control ever waivers—even\nfor a moment—the cost will be your life.
I am aware of the risks.
It is the natural function of a sealer to\nremove dangerous relics; there is no cost\ntoo high if it means seeing this done.
Then I will not stop you.
And now, I must excuse myself. I have not\nbeen here for some time, and wish to\nacquaint myself with the local springs.
I will overcome this challenge, Xu Fu.\nTrust in these words above all else.
I must retrieve the Xihe. Wait for me here.
Look, would it really be so bad\nif you just...sealed the thing?
Did you not understand the\nconversation we just had?
No, I understood. But that doesn't mean\nit actually makes SENSE.
I get the plan: You find this thing and\ncarry it around so it doesn't go crazy.
And if you do that, it means this place\nwon't turn into a big empty desert.
But what about YOU? I heard that old guy:\nIf you slip up even once, you're dead.
Such is the duty of a sealer.
See? You're STILL not making sense.

If you seal the Xihe, it won't be pretty.
Folks'll lose their homes and livelihoods,
and some of 'em probably won't come
out of it in one piece.
But humans aren't stupid. We've been\nwandering the world overcoming stuff for\nas long as there's been a world to wander.
If this place used to be a wasteland,\nmaybe it's better if it just goes back\nto being one.
I'm just saying, this might not be the sort\nof problem you need to risk your life for.
I know you think to speak for your human\npeople in this matter, but this is a\nproblem of Qilin design.
The path of the Qilin is one of discipline to\ncompensate for the long, unbroken chain\nof arrogance we forged in antiquity.
We cannot permit our past mistakes\nto cause current problems for others.
Yeah, and that's an honorable way\nof thinking—but this is your LIFE\nwe're talkin' about here.
Allay your fears. I will control the Xihe,\nand my life will continue as before.
Now please wait here while I\nretrieve the relic.
Are all Qilin this damn stubborn?
Xu Fu certainly seemed to think she was\na special case. ...Well then, my friend?\nWhat do you intend to do?
It's like the wife always says...
It takes a mule to stop a mule.
Your wife sounds like a woman of great\nwisdom. Perhaps you would allow another\nstubborn mule to accompany you?
Wait, really? You know I'm going to\nconvince her to seal away one of those\nrelics you love so much, right?

While the thought of sealing the Xihe is
vexing, we will never be able to unmask
the power of Qilin relics if we lose
Master Xuan Zang.
Sort of a creepy way to think about it,\nbut works for me. Let's get going!
Indeed, my friend! Off we go!
